Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper presents a new approach for distributed gradient descent. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the convergence and performance of the proposed method on real world datasets. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper employs approximate gradient coding to mitigate system delays. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with distributed systems and their performance. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is relevant as the paper discusses the impact of delays on distributed gradient descent.
